question.box:
A catalyst speeds up a reaction. What other single change will make each
of these reactions go faster?



	\mbox{A  Cl_2(g) + H_2(g)  →  2HCl(g)   Δ}H\mbox{ = –184 kJ}



	\mbox{B  CH_4(g) + NH_3(g)  →  HCN(g) + 3H_2(g)   Δ}H\mbox{ = +256 kJ}



	\mbox{C  HClO(aq)  →  H^+(aq) + ClO^–(aq)   Δ}H\mbox{ = +13.8 kJ}



	\mbox{D  N_2(g) + 3H_2(g)  →  2NH_3(g)   Δ}H\mbox{ = –93 kJ}



	\mbox{E  S_2O_8}\mbox{^{2–}(aq) + 2I^–(aq)  →  I_2(aq) + 2SO_4}\mbox{^{2–}(aq)   Δ}H\mbox{ = –341 kJ}



	\mbox{F  2SO_2(g) + O_2(g)  →  2SO_3(g)   Δ}H\mbox{ = –198 kJ}



	\mbox{G  2H_2(g) + O_2(g)  →  2H_2O(g)   Δ}H\mbox{ = –482 kJ}
